The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Sunday, November 14, 2004 

 Undertrial escapes 

 A STAFF REPORTER 

 Calcutta, Nov. 13: An undertrial admitted to SSKM hospital with withdrawal symptoms escaped today. 

 Officials at Maidan police station said 20-year-old Sheikh Firoze Raju was arrested on Tuesday while fleeing with a snatched bag containing Rs 2 lakh. He was admitted to the hospital on Thursday after convulsions, a problem common with persons dependent on narcotics, one official said. 

 The hospital authorities have ordered a probe. 

 Another undertrial died while being taken to SSKM hospital from Alipore central jail this morning. 

 Jail officials said Girindranath Mondal, 49, was being shifted after he complained of chest pain. Mondal was arrested from Gosaba on charges of theft and was brought to the jail on October 27. 




